-- Saudi Fransi Loan Provisions Rise 55% in Second Quarter to $22.4 Million
-- Mourad Haroutunian
-- 2010-07-28T11:27:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-28/saudi-fransi-loan-provisions-rise-55-in-second-quarter-to-22-4-million.html

          
          
             Banque Saudi Fransi , a Saudi lender
part-owned by Credit Agricole SA, posted a 55 percent increase
in provisions for bad loans in the second quarter.  
 The Riyadh-based bank raised provisions to 83.9 million
riyals ($22.4 million) in the three months ended June 30, from
53.9 million riyals in the previous quarter, according to data
posted on the  Saudi bourse  website today.  
 Banque Saudi Fransi â€™s second-quarter profit rose 9.4
percent to 757 million riyals, the lender said in a statement on
July 10.  
